what are your favourite ways to give someone a non body based compliment?
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
it's my favourite way to compliment my friends and family! people are so much more than their body! 
compliments are free, from the heart and have the #PowerToTransform someone’s mood! I’m excited to partner with @Pantene on this campaign because I truly believe compliments have the power to transform someone’s day.
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
compliments actually go a long way in CONNECTING ourselves to others. A @pantene study found that 77% of canadians have felt disconnected from their friends and family during this time and yet 79% of canadians found a compliment can go a LONG way to making them feel better.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
compliments that are genuine are never superficial and never get old. on top of that, we should be giving them to ourselves too! 
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
make someone's day a bit brighter! #PowerToTransform #partner #ad

abuse girls face on social media. Every day girls are physically threatened, racially abused, sexually harassed and body shamed.

Girls from across the world have written an open letter to Instagram, Facebook, TikTok and Twitter, calling on them to create stronger and more effective ways to report abuse and harassment. Sign their open letter now – link in my story – and show that thousands of people stand with girls #FreeToBeOnline online, they’ll be taken seriously #StoptheSetback

node.text: my general take on what’s happening as of now. of course i didn’t get to say everything that i wanted to say and didn’t say everything right. it is a WILD time that we are living in. be prepared to be uncomfortable. be grateful we all still have internet, running water and food. (some of us actually still don’t have those things) and most of all, be grateful we have each other. it sounds corny as hell, but you don’t have your food or toilet paper or internet or water without the help of another human. don’t buy 250 rolls of toilet paper, it’s not the diarrhea boogeyman coming for you. also, what happens after this? do we go back to normal life? will there be a normal life? do you even WANT your normal life back? this is going to be a huge shift for many of us. your emotional shit is going to come up because we don’t have the same comforts as before. be kind and stay vigilant and stay aware! ✌️💕

node.text:
i used to be so *embarrassed* about my body.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
embarrassed like it did something wrong. there would be times i would even apologize for it, simply for existing.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“i’m sorry about my scars”
“i’m so sorry about my stretch marks”
“i’m sorry my breasts”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
covering up and hiding felt so safe and so good. people would make fun of me for wearing sweaters in the summertime and partners would beg to see my body beyond the sheets and in the light, but i didn’t care. i would take any joke and i would lose any person if it meant that i could stay covered.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i would tell partners to leave if they didn’t like it. it would actually be better if they did, i work best on my own. hidden. alone. away.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but eventually there’s a little voice that just won’t shut up. it says stuff about love, about dreams, about the world and it begs you to explore. to be touched. to be adored. to be seen.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
in small moments you shut it up or you quietly listen. and in the moments you quietly listen your shame, guilt and hatred begin to transform into curiosity, love and passion.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
it’s okay if you’re not there yet either! it takes a thousand moments of listening to that small voice and choosing the unknown, over and over and over again ❤️
#selfgrowth #selflovejourney #youareloved

node.text:
the other day a friend came over and i thought to myself "do i have to be kenzie brenna or can i tell her i'm having a bad day?"
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i was feeling so insecure about many things, it was hard to appreciate the mountains in front of me and the moment's were slipping out of my hands.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
sometimes i feel like i need to be "on" for people. i need to be happy! inspiring! confident! brave! say things that are motivating! say things that will change people lives! be an attentive listener! ask the best questions! that's why people like me right?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
when really i'm terrible and i want to fall into the hands of another and let life be grey, sad and uninspiring. i want to be messy and insecure and fragile, but i'm so caught up in whether or not that will make me *less desirable* that i tone it down. i hold those moments in just for myself, i manage on my own.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
it's tough admitting this because i tell people to vulnerable and be themselves all the time when i have a hard time doing it with those closest to me.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the broken down, weird, tired, annoying, dull, uninspiring person lives in all of us. we don't have to people please or act our way out of it. at least that's the message i'm giving myself today.
📸 - @jessica.bate_

node.text:
this last year has been wild to watch the ways social media has influenced how we treat one another.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i’ve seen people say “cancel culture doesn’t exist, it’s accountability that everyone is hiding from.” and then i would watch my friends be harassed, doxxed, stalked, be sent death threats, lose their jobs, become depressed, toy with suicidality and live in fear.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
and these friends come from different backgrounds. some white, some Black, some Indigenous, some Jewish, some rich, some poor, some with big accounts, some with small accounts and so on. so we need to cut the shit when we think that cancel culture only comes for the rich white men of the world because it doesn’t. it comes for all of us.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
reading anti racism books and books on healing in general, it always came back that these tactics for accountability are actually the antithesis of what accountability truly is.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
that’s why i speak out about it because treating each other as disposable and basing our entire beings off of a bad thing we have done is not conducive to the utopia we want to be build. humans are complex, smart, stupid, annoying, progressive, beautiful and ugly all the same time.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
and i choose to look at people like they are part of nature. growing. evolving. not frozen or static. but fluid and dynamic.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
so if you’ve said or done anything harmful in the past (or in the future) you have a deep responsibility to come to terms with it and figure out a way to repair that for yourself and others. i’m also not an authority or expert on how that looks, nor is a single member from a community.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i don’t get to throw people in the garbage just because it’s more convenient than actually doing the work to help create an environment where accountability is supported and encouraged.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i’m excited fo hear everyone’s thoughts on the topic and also excited to disagree with one another :)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
📃 from my beautiful friend @seerutkchawla

node.text:
sometimes grocery shopping exhausts me.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i don’t mean for it to, but i stop and think about every single thing i put in my cart. i think about it’s nutrition, i think about its carbon footprint, i think about the underpaid workers who picked it, the farmers who grew it, how it will affect my body once i eat it, whether it will make me happy or disappointed, whether i’ll actually eat it or just end up throwing it out or if i’m a good person for buying it or a bad person for buying it, is it a food that will contribute to my ED or will it be helpful for me?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
and then i think of the ways i feel guilty that i only worked, meditated, meal prepped that day, why didn’t i make more time to stretch and workout? “good people make time for those things, you’re not good.”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
and then i make some dinner and it’s broccoli and tofu dogs and i think about how tofu can fuck up my cystic acne but at least the tofu dogs are high in protein which helps curb bingeing, so if i have to choose, i choose that.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
then i make tea with stevia, not honey, stevia. i’m lucky i actually like it but it sure as hell isn’t the beautiful rich taste of honey.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
eating is supposed to be “easy” and it never is and i’ve given up on the idea that it ever will be.

this is a sticky subject no doubt but with the recent texas law i feel heartbroken for all the people who may potentially get sued for doing something that is healthy and important for women/peoples bodies.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the data speaks for itself.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
• abortions ONLY decline when contraception and sex education go up.
• abortions have been decreasing worldwide the more that countries legalize them and increase sex education and availability to contraception.
• making abortions illegal or deputizing people to sue others for having them will not decrease abortions. they statistically just make them more unsafe which actually results in public health issues. this is due to the post medical issues a person has when they are done illegally and unsafe. seven women/people per hour die from medical complications due to unsafe abortions.
• let alone the staggering stats that have constantly shown that when abortions are accessible and safe women/people not only do not regret their decision but feel it saved their lives and decreased psychological stress.
• lastly, while yes men have historically made decisions for women’s bodies, the numbers are in that just as many if not more women than men are supporting anti abortion laws. women are just as capable as being hateful and uneducated as men are when it comes to this pro choice discussion and seeing inflammatory things like “i don’t see many men discussing this” i think it’s divisive and unhelpful during a time when we just need to be asking for allies from literally any gender.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i’ve never talked about abortion on this page but i hope that it’s clear i’m very pro choice and believe in safe accessible funded health care for all.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
